# Joseph as chief administrator of Egypt — national famine-management plan.
# Phase artifact: foreign-buyers (domain fragment). foreign buyers are registered after local scarcity and supplied.
# One admitted PDDL Turtle planning artifact; fragments across all phase
# artifacts merge structurally into ONE combined plan (domain name
# 'joseph-famine' shared by every fragment). Formal planning-to-workflow
# demonstration domain; argues no doctrine, claims no historicity.
@prefix ex: <http://example.org/joseph#> .
@prefix ceng: <urn:chatman:engine#> .

ex:foreign-buyers ex:request ex:grain .

ex:foreign-buyers ceng:pddlDomain """
(define (domain joseph-famine)
  (:requirements :strips)
  (:predicates
    (treasury-updated ?x)
    (foreign-buyers-registered ?x)
    (foreign-buyers-supplied ?x))
  (:action register-foreign-buyers
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (treasury-updated ?x))
    :effect (and (foreign-buyers-registered ?x)))
  (:action supply-foreign-buyers
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (foreign-buyers-registered ?x))
    :effect (and (foreign-buyers-supplied ?x))))
""" .
